# Scratch / ephemeral directories produced by gate scripts (install_consumer,
# benchmark snapshots, ad-hoc agent tooling).  NEVER committed; playbooks in
# docs/AGENTS.md and tools/check_repo_artifacts.sh enforce this.
.tmp_gate*/
.tmp_*/

# Canonical build dir used by build-fast.sh (BUILD_DIR_OVERRIDE-defaulted to
# `${ROOT_DIR}/.tmp/chronon-builds/<preset>`).  NEVER committed: contains
# build.ninja, CMakeCache.txt, *.ninja_log, compile_commands.json etc., which
# leak absolute build-machine paths.  AGENTS.md § anti-artefact invariant:
# never commit build output.  Without this rule, every machine leaves an
# untracked entry in `git status` that breaks tools/check_main_clean.sh's
# "working tree dirty" gate (the gate enforces the invariant); the other
# .tmp_* patterns above are gate-pipeline-specific and do not cover the
# bare `.tmp/` project-local build root.
/.tmp/

# Local git worktrees (parallel agent branches — never on main)
.worktrees/
.build-tmp/
.git_tmp_*

# CI gate pipeline temporary build dirs (.tmp_gate10/, .tmp_gate11/, …).
# Generated by CMake/ninja under gate-pipeline runs (`tools/check_*.sh`,
# `tools/install_consumer_test.sh`, etc.) and MUST NEVER enter the git
# index: their generated files (build.ninja, CMakeCache.txt, .ninja_deps,
# CTestTestfile.cmake, compile_commands.json) leak absolute build-machine
# paths (e.g. /home/<user>/Pyt/Chronon3d/...).  Hardened audit:
#     tools/check_gitignored_dirs.sh   (Fase 0 — tracked-glob + abs-path)
.tmp_gate*/

# Build resource logging dirs (vcpkg-manifest-install.log artifacts).
# Phase-0 close-out: these were tracked with machine-specific absolute
# paths inside their log files; de-tracked and excluded at root.
/build_text_res_*/

# Partner-owned Refactor 1B overlay (text preset catalog split) — gitignored
# to keep GATE-MNT-01 clean for everyone.  Canonical registry path is
# `cmake/Chronon3DRegistry.cmake`, NOT this directory.  Partner commit
# `8d5ed596` (presets: bump version...) did not include these files; they
# are deferred indefinitely.  See `docs/FOLLOWUP_TICKETS.md` TICKET-062.
/src/registry/text/

# Local idempotency scratch helpers (Agent3 atomic-commit tooling) —
# underscore prefix signals "ephemeral, not project-owned".  These are
# re-run-on-demand scripts (e.g. `_sect12_stub.py` to restore a missing
# doc section, `_span_name_closure.py` for batch edits) and are NOT
# durable project tooling.  See `docs/FOLLOWUP_TICKETS.md` TICKET-063.
tools/_*.py
sdk_consumer_output.png
reports/perf/

# ── Dashboard frontend build artifacts ────────────────────────────────────────
# AGENTS.md v0.1 § anti-artefact invariant: NEVER commit dist/ or node_modules/.
# Frontend lives at tools/telemetry_dashboard/frontend/ and is rebuilt fresh
# on demand via `cd tools/telemetry_dashboard/frontend && npm install && npm run build`.
# Both scoped here (dashboard-specific paths) AND globally (fallback for any
# future frontend apps + raw npm/yarn dependency caches).
tools/telemetry_dashboard/frontend/dist/
tools/telemetry_dashboard/frontend/node_modules/

# Global fallback (belt-and-suspenders against future accidental git add .)
dist/
node_modules/
artifacts/
test_output/

# Auto-emitted golden-diff artifact subdirs (created by tests/visual/support/golden_test.hpp
# when verify_golden produces a mismatch).  Transient by design — regenerated per
# run and never recomputed into goldens.  Listed explicitly (not `**/diff/`) so the
# tracked `tests/golden/ae_parity/` parent remains indexable.
tests/golden/ae_parity/diff/

# BUG 2 / TICKET-TEXT-GLOW-DARKENING — Step 3 A/B test outputs (transient
# experiment PNGs regenerated per `chronon3d_cli render` invocation, never
# recomputed into goldens).  Mirrors the `tests/golden/ae_parity/diff/`
# pattern above: tracked repo holds the experiment SOURCES (composition,
# script, report), the rendered PNGs are ephemeral.  See
# docs/baselines/2026-07-10-glow-ab-result.md for reproduction commands.
tests/visual/glow_with/
tests/visual/glow_without/

# AE-parity referee engine output (TICKET-AE-PARITY-DRIVER).  The AE-side
# mocks at `reference/after_effects/*.png` are manually committed; the
# engine output at `reference/chronon3d/*.png` is regenerated per ctest run
# and MUST stay out of git to keep `git status` clean.  The `*.gitkeep`
# placeholders are preserved (they don't match `*.png`).
reference/chronon3d/*.png
tools/telemetry_dashboard/.vite/
.ccache/

# Build output directory (chronon-builds artifacts)
.tmp/

# Cert-run log artifacts (transient by design — e.g. `tmp/baseline-<sha>/A1..B7..C..E.log` produced by fresh `docs/baselines/main-<sha>-baseline.md` runs; regenerated per cert invocation, never recomputed into git — cert rationale: see `docs/baselines/main-908c7034-baseline.md` Forensic-replay section + AGENTS.md §honesty §"Non committare ... output, artefatti o file generati").  Without this rule, every cert run leaves an untracked `tmp/baseline-*/` that breaks `tools/check_main_clean.sh`'s "working tree dirty" gate.  Mirrors the `.tmp_gate*/` and `.tmp/chronon-builds/` patterns above.
tmp/
